<br />
<br />Now for something more on topic:
<br />
<br />A few years ago I wasn't being productive and my family was not happy about that.
<br />
<br />The turning point for me was deciding that instead of just going back to college and hoping my dream job would fall into my lap, I would be proactive and make it happen.  I thought my family would think that transfering to a school to pursue a game-programming degree was silly, but they were actually just glad to see me be independent and pursue my passion.</div>

